   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## Gaudin Lax matrix\n\nBuilds the single-site Gaudin Lax matrix $L(z)$ from the $\\mathfrak{su}(4)$ generators $e_{ij} = J_{ij}$ acting on the representation `rep`: $L(z)_{ij} = p_j\\,\\delta_{ij} + \\dfrac{e_{ji}}{z - w_1}$, with a simple pole at the marked point $w_1$ and diagonal inhomogeneities $p_j$.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ee[rep_][i_,j_] := JJ[i,j,rep];\n\nLL[rep_][i_,j_][z_] := p[j] KroneckerDelta[i,j] IdentityMatrix[dim[rep]] + ee[rep][j,i]/(z - w[1]);",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## Quantum determinant and Talalaev's construction\n\nConstructs the quantum (Capelli) determinant $\\det{}_q(\\partial_z + L(z))$ of the Gaudin Lax matrix via the epsilon-epsilon expansion $\\det A = \\frac{1}{N!}\\sum_{I,J} \\epsilon_I \\epsilon_J\\, A_{i_1 j_1}\\cdots A_{i_N j_N}$, applied noncommutatively since $L(z)$ does not commute with $\\partial_z$ (Talalaev's construction). The block is kept generic in the abstract Lax matrix `L[i,j][z]`, to be specialized later via `L -> LL[rep]` (or a multi-site version). The result is expanded as a differential operator $\\partial_z^4 + H[1](z)\\,\\partial_z^3 + H[2](z)\\,\\partial_z^2 + H[3](z)\\,\\partial_z + H[4](z)$ acting on $f(z)$, and $H[1..4](z)$ are the generating functions whose residues at the marked points give the commuting Gaudin Hamiltonians.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "$M_{ij}[f] = \\partial_z f\\,\\delta_{ij} + L(z)_{ij}\\cdot f$, the $(i,j)$ entry of the operator $(\\partial_z\\cdot\\mathrm{Id} + L(z))$ acting on $f(z)$.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "M[{i_, j_}][f_] := D[f, z] KroneckerDelta[i, j] + L[i, j][z] . f;",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Expands a length-4 index chain `MChain[{a,b,c,d}]` into the nested operator composition $M_a\\circ M_b\\circ M_c\\circ M_d$ applied to $f(z)$, distributing `Dot` (noncommutative composition) over sums to keep the expansion linear.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "applyMs = {\n   MChain[{a__, b__, c__, d__}] :> M[a][M[b][M[c][M[d][f[z]]]]] //.\n     Dot[a___, b_ + c_, d___] :> Dot[a, b, d] + Dot[a, c, d]\n  };",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "The $\\epsilon$-$\\epsilon$ contraction term: sums $\\mathrm{sign}(\\sigma)$ over permutations $\\sigma$ matching $I_\\sigma$ to $J$ (zero unless $I$ is a permutation of $J$), weighting the ordered operator chain `MChain[Transpose[{I,J}]]`.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "EE[II_, JJ_] :=\n  1/4! Sum[\n     Signature[\\[Sigma]] Times @@ (e[#] & /@ Transpose[{II[[\\[Sigma]]], JJ}]),\n     {\\[Sigma], Permutations[{1, 2, 3, 4}]}\n    ] MChain[Transpose[{II, JJ}]] /. e[{a_, b_}] :> KroneckerDelta[a, b];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Sums `EE[I,J]` over all index tuples $I,J\\in\\{1,\\dots,4\\}^4$, i.e. the identity $\\det A = \\frac{1}{N!}\\sum_{I,J} \\epsilon_I \\epsilon_J\\, A_{i_1 j_1}\\cdots A_{i_N j_N}$ applied noncommutatively (scalars are pulled through `Dot`, but $L$ never crosses past $\\partial_z$/$f$), collapsing the result into a differential operator in $z$ acting on $f(z)$.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "detOp =\n  (Sum[EE[II, JJ], {II, Tuples[Range[4], 4]}, {JJ, Tuples[Range[4], 4]}] //. applyMs // ExpandAll) //.\n    Dot[a___, b_ + c_, d___] :> Dot[a, b, d] + Dot[a, c, d] //.\n    Dot[a___, b_, d___] :> b Dot[a, d] /; FreeQ[b, f | L] //.\n    Dot[a___, b_*c_, d___] :> b Dot[a, c, d] /; FreeQ[b, L] //.\n    Dot[a___, f'''[z]] :> Dot[a] f'''[z] //.\n    Dot[a___, f''[z]] :> Dot[a] f''[z] //.\n    Dot[a___, f'[z]] :> Dot[a] f'[z] //.\n    Dot[a___, f[z]] :> Dot[a] f[z]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Reads off the coefficients of $f'''(z), f''(z), f'(z), f(z)$ to give $H_1(z),\\dots,H_4(z)$, the Talalaev generating functions for the commuting Gaudin Hamiltonians.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "H[1][z_] = Coefficient[detOp, f'''[z]];\nH[2][z_] = Coefficient[detOp, f''[z]] // ExpandAll;\nH[3][z_] = Coefficient[detOp, f'[z]] // ExpandAll;\nH[4][z_] = Coefficient[detOp, f[z]] // ExpandAll;",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## SU(3) determinant limit: contour-integral building block\n\nBefore specializing the quantum determinant construction above, we isolate one small primitive that will be reused when deriving the $\\mathfrak{su}(3)$ determinant as a limiting case of the $\\mathfrak{su}(4)$ one: a contour integral of an arbitrary (pole-free) function $f(u)$ against the two-point Gaudin measure $\\mu(u) = \\dfrac{1}{(u-\\theta)(u-\\theta-h)}$, taken around a contour encircling both poles $u=\\theta,\\theta+h$. This is *not* yet the SU(3) determinant itself — just the building block.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {
    "toolId": "X23sZmlsZQ%3D%3D"
   }
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Defines the measure `mu[u,theta,h]` with simple poles at $u=\\theta$ and $u=\\theta+h$, and `gaudinMeasureResidue[expr,theta,h]`, the sum of the residues of $\\mathrm{expr}(u)\\,\\mu(u)$ at those two poles — i.e. $\\dfrac{1}{2\\pi i}\\oint \\mathrm{expr}(u)\\,\\mu(u)\\,du$ around a contour enclosing both poles. Here `expr` is a *bare expression in the symbol* `u` (the same `u` used in `mu`), e.g. `u^3` or `Exp[k u]` — not a function head — so no `Function[]`/`#&` wrapping is needed; `expr` is assumed to have no poles inside the contour.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {
    "toolId": "X24sZmlsZQ%3D%3D"
   }
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[mu, gaudinMeasureResidue];\n\nmu[u_, theta_, h_] := 1/((u - theta) (u - theta - h));\n\ngaudinMeasureResidue[expr_, theta_, h_] :=\n  Simplify[\n   Residue[expr mu[u, theta, h], {u, theta}] +\n    Residue[expr mu[u, theta, h], {u, theta + h}]];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {
    "toolId": "X25sZmlsZQ%3D%3D"
   }
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Checks the reduction symbolically for a generic black-box expression $f_0(u)$ (i.e. `f0[u]`, plain in the variable `u`): since both poles are simple, $\\mathrm{Res}_{u=\\theta} = -f_0(\\theta)/h$ and $\\mathrm{Res}_{u=\\theta+h} = f_0(\\theta+h)/h$, so the sum should collapse to the finite difference $(f_0(\\theta+h)-f_0(\\theta))/h$.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {
    "toolId": "X26sZmlsZQ%3D%3D"
   }
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[finiteDiff];\n\n(* substitution-based finite difference: expr is a bare expression in u, not a function head *)\nfiniteDiff[expr_, theta_, h_] := ((expr /. u -> theta + h) - (expr /. u -> theta))/h;\n\ngenericResult = gaudinMeasureResidue[f0[u], theta, h];\ngenericTarget = finiteDiff[f0[u], theta, h];\n\n{genericResult, genericTarget, Simplify[genericResult - genericTarget] === 0}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"445753\" data-output-id=\"5\" data-out-n=\"28\" data-sub-idx=\"5\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"21\" data-sub-start=\"8\" data-sub-end=\"8\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[28]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrhoqiji-n8zuld7\" data-page-width-em=\"36\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1xmcmFje2YwXGxlZnQoaCtcbWF0aHJte3RoZXRhfVxyaWdodCktZjBcbGVmdChcbWF0aHJte3RoZXRhfVxyaWdodCl9e2h9LFxmcmFje2YwXGxlZnQoaCtcbWF0aHJte3RoZXRhfVxyaWdodCktZjBcbGVmdChcbWF0aHJte3RoZXRhfVxyaWdodCl9e2h9LFxtYXRocm17VHJ1ZX1ccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.4em;vertical-align:-0.95em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">{</span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.427em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">theta</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">theta</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.427em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">theta</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">theta</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">True</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[28]= \\left\\{\\frac{f0\\left(h+\\mathrm{theta}\\right)-f0\\left(\\mathrm{theta}\\right)}{h},\\frac{f0\\left(h+\\mathrm{theta}\\right)-f0\\left(\\mathrm{theta}\\right)}{h},\\mathrm{True}\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "bc07ec34-a4e9-42d2-809c-618344d28a7f"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "toolId": "X30sZmlsZQ%3D%3D"
   }
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Validates on concrete pole-free test expressions in `u` (polynomial, exponential, trig, and a symbolic-rate exponential $e^{k u}$ — no test expression may have a pole near $\\theta,\\theta+h$, unlike e.g. $1/(u+5)$), comparing `gaudinMeasureResidue[expr,theta,h]` against the direct finite difference `finiteDiff[expr,theta,h]` both symbolically (generic $\\theta,h$) and numerically (specific values). The $e^{ku}$ case specifically covers the bare-expression calling convention (`gaudinMeasureResidue[Exp[k u], theta, h]`) rather than a `Function[]`-wrapped one.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {
    "toolId": "X31sZmlsZQ%3D%3D"
   }
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "testExprs = {u^3, Exp[u], Sin[u], Exp[k u]};\n\n(* symbolic check: generic theta, h *)\nsymbolicChecks = Simplify[gaudinMeasureResidue[#, theta, h] - finiteDiff[#, theta, h]] & /@ testExprs;\n\n(* exact-rational check at specific theta, h: Simplify to confirm the exact difference vanishes *)\nexactChecks = Simplify[gaudinMeasureResidue[#, 7/3, 11/5] - finiteDiff[#, 7/3, 11/5]] & /@ testExprs;\n\n(* numeric (floating-point) check at specific theta, h; also substitute a numeric rate k for the Exp[k u] case *)\nnumericChecks = Chop[N[(gaudinMeasureResidue[#, 7/3, 11/5] - finiteDiff[#, 7/3, 11/5]) /. k -> 3/2]] & /@ testExprs;\n\n{symbolicChecks, exactChecks, numericChecks}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"445753\" data-output-id=\"6\" data-out-n=\"33\" data-sub-idx=\"7\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"23\" data-sub-start=\"11\" data-sub-end=\"11\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[33]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrhoqirk-fetp1e5\" data-page-width-em=\"18\" data-latex-b64=\"XGJlZ2lue3BtYXRyaXh9MCAmIDAgJiAwICYgMFxcMCAmIDAgJiAwICYgMFxcMCAmIDAgJiAwICYgMFxlbmR7cG1hdHJpeH0=\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:3.6em;vertical-align:-1.55em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen\"><span class=\"delimsizing mult\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-4.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:5.6em;\"></span><span style=\"width:0.875em;height:3.600em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.875em\" height=\"3.600em\" viewBox=\"0 0 875 3600\"><path d=\"M863,9c0,-2,-2,-5,-6,-9c0,0,-17,0,-17,0c-12.7,0,-19.3,0.3,-20,1\nc-5.3,5.3,-10.3,11,-15,17c-242.7,294.7,-395.3,682,-458,1162c-21.3,163.3,-33.3,349,\n-36,557 l0,84c0.2,6,0,26,0,60c2,159.3,10,310.7,24,454c53.3,528,210,\n949.7,470,1265c4.7,6,9.7,11.7,15,17c0.7,0.7,7,1,19,1c0,0,18,0,18,0c4,-4,6,-7,6,-9\nc0,-2.7,-3.3,-8.7,-10,-18c-135.3,-192.7,-235.5,-414.3,-300.5,-665c-65,-250.7,-102.5,\n-544.7,-112.5,-882c-2,-104,-3,-167,-3,-189\nl0,-92c0,-162.7,5.7,-314,17,-454c20.7,-272,63.7,-513,129,-723c65.3,\n-210,155.3,-396.3,270,-559c6.7,-9.3,10,-15.3,10,-18z\"/></svg></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.55em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mtable\"><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-4.21em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.01em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-1.81em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.55em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-4.21em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.01em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-1.81em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.55em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-4.21em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.01em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-1.81em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.55em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-4.21em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.01em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-1.81em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.55em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"delimsizing mult\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:2.05em;\"><span style=\"top:-4.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:5.6em;\"></span><span style=\"width:0.875em;height:3.600em;\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"0.875em\" height=\"3.600em\" viewBox=\"0 0 875 3600\"><path d=\"M76,0c-16.7,0,-25,3,-25,9c0,2,2,6.3,6,13c21.3,28.7,42.3,60.3,\n63,95c96.7,156.7,172.8,332.5,228.5,527.5c55.7,195,92.8,416.5,111.5,664.5\nc11.3,139.3,17,290.7,17,454c0,28,1.7,43,3.3,45l0,9\nc-3,4,-3.3,16.7,-3.3,38c0,162,-5.7,313.7,-17,455c-18.7,248,-55.8,469.3,-111.5,664\nc-55.7,194.7,-131.8,370.3,-228.5,527c-20.7,34.7,-41.7,66.3,-63,95c-2,3.3,-4,7,-6,11\nc0,7.3,5.7,11,17,11c0,0,11,0,11,0c9.3,0,14.3,-0.3,15,-1c5.3,-5.3,10.3,-11,15,-17\nc242.7,-294.7,395.3,-681.7,458,-1161c21.3,-164.7,33.3,-350.7,36,-558\nl0,-144c-2,-159.3,-10,-310.7,-24,-454c-53.3,-528,-210,-949.7,\n-470,-1265c-4.7,-6,-9.7,-11.7,-15,-17c-0.7,-0.7,-6.7,-1,-18,-1z\"/></svg></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.55em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
